# PyCharm
#  JetBrains specific template is maintained in a separate JetBr
#  be found at https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/Glo
#  and can be added to the global gitignore or merged into this one. If you want to ignore all JetBrains IDEs, you can add the following line to your .gitignore file:
#  option (not recommended) you can uncomment the following to i
#.idea/
# Ignore Django Migrations in Development if you are working on a Django project. This allows you to keep your migration files in version control while ignoring the generated migration files that are created during development. This is useful because migration files can be generated frequently and may not need to be tracked in version control, especially if they are not intended to be shared with other developers or deployed to production. By ignoring the migrations directory, you can avoid cluttering your version control history with unnecessary migration files while still keeping the important ones that are needed for the project.
# Only for Development only
**/migrations/**
!**/migrations
!**/migrations/__init__.py
